article.headline: VCU 72, S. Dakota St. 56
article.story: RICHMOND, Va. -- Eric Maynor scored 16 of his 29 points during a 24-7 second-half spurt, leading Virginia Commonwealth to a 72-56 win over South Dakota State Wednesday night. Maynor added five assists for the Rams (2-0), and Kirill Pishchalnikov added six points and 10 rebounds. The Rams rushed to a 25-9 lead with 10:25 left in the first half, hitting 10 of their first 14 shots. The Jackrabbits (1-2) ran off the next 10 points led by a pair of 3-pointers from Clint Sargent to trail 25-19 with 6:21 left. The Rams went into the locker room with a 38-30 lead. Garrett Callahan led the Jackrabbits with 21 points and Sargent added 20. South Dakota State out rebounded Virginia Commonwealth 41-38, as Anthony Cordova grabbed 11 rebounds and Sargent had 10 to set career highs for both players.
